{"lemma":"مِفْتاحِ","slug":"مِفْتاحِ","root":"ف.ت.ح","root_slug":"ف-ت-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32894"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D9%81%D9%92%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"key (to a door)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"key (on a piano or other keyboard instrument)","examples":[{"text":"لَوْحَةُ مَفَاتِيحَ","english":"keyboard"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"key (crucial step)","tags":["figuratively"],"examples":[{"text":"مِفْتَاحُ ٱلسَّعَادَةِ","english":"key of happiness"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun from the verb فَتَحَ (fataḥa, “to open”). Compare Hebrew מַפְתֵּחַ (maftéakh)."},"ipa":["/mif.taːħ/","/muf.taːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32894","headword_ar":"مِفْتَاحٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifotaHN","text_ar":"مِفْتَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A key; an instrument with which a lock is opened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a key"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a door; and of anything that is closed, or locked; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an instrument for opening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything with which a thing is opened:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAtiyHu","text_ar":"مَفَاتِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfaAtiHu","text_ar":"مفَاتِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said by Akh to be similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaAniY~u","text_ar":"اَمَانِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaAnK","text_ar":"اَمَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfAtyH","text_ar":"مفاتيح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifotaAHN","text_ar":"مِفْتَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfAtH","text_ar":"مفاتح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifotaHN","text_ar":"مِفْتَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as well as of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafotaHN","text_ar":"مَفْتَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifotaAHuhaA AlT~uhuwru","text_ar":"مِفْتَاحُهَا الطُّهُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said by the Prophet, in relation to prayer, means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That which is as though it were the key thereof is the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one purifies himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the means of removing the legal impurity that prevents one's addressing himself boldly to the act of prayer. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwitiytu mafaAtiyHa Alkalimi","text_ar":"اُوِتِيتُ مَفَاتِيحَ الكَلِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAtiHa","text_ar":"مَفَاتِحَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalimi","text_ar":"الكَلِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different relaters, occurring in a trad., i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have been given the keys of words,"},{"kind":"text","text":"means [I have been given] an easy faculty, granted by God, for the acquirement of eloquence and chasteness of speech, and the attaining to the understanding of obscure meanings, and novel and admirable kinds of knowledge, and the beauties of expressions and phrases, which are closed against others, and difficult to be learnt by them. (L.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmifotaAHu","text_ar":"المِفْتَاحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain brand upon the thigh and neck"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel, in the form of what is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"properly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thus called."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}